{"title":"Tunisia Diaries: From London to Girondelle","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tunisia-diaries-london-to-girondelle","date":1686751909000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tunisia-diaries-london-to-girondelle\">Tunisia Diaries: From London to Girondelle</a></p>\n\n<p>I’m on my way to Tunisia in case you haven’t heard, and so far the journey is proving to be quite the adventure. Not least because I have chosen to ride in the absolutely sweltering heat. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>From mornings with gravel, to lunchtime cobbles and roasting afternoon asphalt, the routes I’ve ridden so far have been for the large part scenic and peaceful.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Mostly it’s been a case of winding through French and Belgian farmland, ducking out the way of tractors and muting the voice in my head which is convinced the cows are going to escape their field and chase me.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing like a good bit of motivation though. I’m 426.11 kilometres down, which feels like a lot, but there’s still a long way to go.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ribble-gravel-ti\">Tunisia Diaries: This is the bike I’m riding to Tunisia </a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-bike-fit\">Tunisia Diaries: I’m cycling 2,311km so it’s time for a bike-fit</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-kit-list\">Tunisia Diaries: What I’m packing to ride 2,311km in 16 days</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>London to Autingues</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-1.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Led by my friend Anca, we met in Peckham and together rolled our way through Greenwich Park, to Dartford and Rochester. Having left at 5am, the morning was blissful with minimal traffic and generally decent cycleways.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A whisker before Canterbury, emergency works stood in our way. The only way round (save for a big detour) was to wiggle along some footpaths before hauling our bikes up 10 flights of stairs. I wouldn’t describe it as a hoot.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, the 97km to Canterbury breezed by. A quick sandwich was consumed among the throng of tourists, and we headed out to the last tranche before the white cliffs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"728\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-728x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-728x970.jpg 728w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-750x1000.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2-1140x1520.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-2.jpg 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It could have been the sandwich, the 28 degree heat, or simply just me, but the last 30km or so felt like a lifetime, not helped by a fellow cyclist remarking, ‘Wow that looks heavy’. As if I didn’t know.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s no denying spirits were waning, Dover felt so close but the undulating hills which lay before us dissolved much hope we would ever see the sea. But lo and behold, what can Abba not do? To the tunes of ‘Mamma Mia’, we rattled down into Dover for an ice cream and I even made the ferry in plenty of time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 15:55 Dover to Calais was my first ferry with a bicycle, and an experience which I would genuinely recommend. At Dover, it was a case of following the red line all the way through passport control, check in and then be let on to the front of the ferry. Once at the other side, I was escorted out of the ferry port nice and safely. What a treat.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-3.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The final leg of my first day involved a 20km ‘cool down’, as I like to call it, to the campsite, Camping Saint Louis, in Autingues. It was predominantly a long, flat and straight road which would best be described as boring. But the campsite was brilliant with a nice restaurant and a good buzz to it. Pizza and beer finished off the day, before I lay down in my tiny little tent. Only to realise once I was in the sleeping bag that I’d placed it on a downward slope.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Distance 150.40km</li><li>Elevation 1,408m</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Autingues to Flines-lès-Mortagne</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 5:20am wake up was welcomed, considering I spent most the night convinced someone was attacking my tent. Not sure why I thought camping was a good idea.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready for some food, I pedalled to the nearby baguette dispensary, to find it empty. Undeterred, I knew some bread couldn’t be too far away. Except it was Monday and people around here don’t seem to do much on Mondays. It took me three hours to find an open boulangerie.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-5.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Onwards and upwards, I found roadworks after roadworks, and meandered through the French countryside before a steady climb and the beating sun broke me into a very decent sweat.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It was scorching. I reached the town of Cassel, which is covered in cobbles, albeit extremely pretty, and marched into Carrefour to replenish my supplies.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I cycled through miles and miles of farmland, with everything from cockerels, cows, cats, mice to rabbits and birds all whittering about their daily lives.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-6.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This tranquility was soon shattered by the industrial noises of Lille, and the countless roadworks hammering away at the city. Alas, tragedy then struck as one of my pannier straps, which prevent rattling, broke and my precious cargo was thrown into the road. Luckily I brought bungee cords so crisis averted.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I thought a segue into Belgium would be fun so I headed towards Tournai, and had my first experience with the Belgian cobbles, or pavé. The sounds of a rickety bicycle with shaking panniers could be heard for miles around. Ok, maybe not, but it felt like it – I proceeded to avoid the pavé where possible after this, which included a long detour where I realised I had run out of water at the hottest time of the year. Not my finest hour.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-7.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Spirit not yet completely sunk, I met a nice man who filled a bottle up with water and ice, and who frankly saved the day. Finally I pootled back into France, to my next campsite, Camping des Poteries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not sure I’ll be going back, but try everything once and all that…</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Distance 145.05km</li><li>Elevation 815m</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Flines-lès-Mortagne to Girondelle</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-10.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I woke up on day three with one thing on my mind: croissants. Within 20 minutes I had found the perfect boulangerie and the day really started with a bang.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Add in a beautiful riverside cycle path, a sweetcorn, cheese and tomato pasta sauce sandwich and things were really rolling well.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, I then popped into Belgium briefly for some more cobbles, before finding myself in Mauberge heading south, and to my great joy on a Voie Verte. A path for everyone bar motorists, a Voie Verte is frankly glorious. I cycled through delectable forests and countryside, all the while mostly in the shade. It was 15 kilometres of utter bliss.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-11.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After a solid amount of salty chips, I headed back into Belgium (why oh why?) for the final time, and for my final climb of the day. Sweeping back across the border into France, I passed through Signy-le-Petit, a quaint typical rural town, with yes more roadworks. I’ve never seen so much road improvement going on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The heat began to sink into my skin. I stopped regularly in the shade, slurping on lukewarm water and shovelling the rest of the salty chips into my mouth. Will this ever end? Funny how the last 40km seemed to be the longest.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, though, the sparse village of Girondelle finally came into sight, and a bedraggled cyclist freewheeled into her <em>chambre des hôtes</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Distance 130.66km</li><li>Elevation 1,024m</li></ul>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tunisia-diaries-london-to-girondelle\">Tunisia Diaries: From London to Girondelle</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Emma Cole &#124; Features Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"85df4a2cd5e896afebfd6439115305b6f9607ac755b63e0483a9c60c56d7c60e","category":"Cycling"}